---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <meta name="description" content="leter.net privacy and data handling policy." />
    <title>Privacy & Data | leter.net</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="min-h-screen bg-surface">
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-text">‚Üê Back to home</a>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Last updated: February 15, 2026</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-muted">
          <p>
            This policy explains how data is handled for the privately administered domain leter.net.
          </p>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">1. Private Domain Infrastructure</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              leter.net is a privately owned personal domain. No public registration or user
              onboarding is offered.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">2. Data Handling</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Email routing and processing are handled by a third-party infrastructure provider
              (Forward Email). Minimal operational logs and metadata may be processed by that
              provider for delivery and security.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Lewsion Ltd. maintains proprietary forensic tooling for DMARC and MTA-STS analysis to
              ensure domain-level integrity. These tools process aggregate security reports only and
              do not access individual message bodies.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">3. Retention</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Security logs and reporting data are retained only as long as necessary for technical
              reliability and abuse prevention, typically under 24 hours unless required for active
              review.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">4. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              leter.net does not use analytics, tracking cookies, or marketing identifiers.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-text">5. Contact</h2>
            <p class="mt-2">
              Privacy concerns: <span class="text-text">abuse@leter.net</span>
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
